Branch standardization is a critical aspect of DevOps that involves establishing guidelines and best practices for creating and managing branches within a version control system (VCS) such as Git. These standards are designed to ensure consistency, collaboration, and efficiency across development teams, particularly in continuous integration and continuous delivery (CI/CD) 

Continuous Integration/Continuous Deployment (CI/CD): Ansible can be integrated into CI/CD pipelines to automate the deployment of applications to Azure App Services as part of a continuous deployment strategy. This helps streamline the development and deployment process.
